text.text:
On our visit to Lucknow, we have stayed at this OYO hotel.  Actually,  we selected the hotel due to its location and 'oyo' brand name.  Sadly,  our experience was simply bad.
The room alloted to us had rotten smell.  They provided an alternative smaller room.
The bathroom was very small resulting in water slippage to the main room.
The persons on the counter were arrogant. Instead of solving the problem,  they have mastered the art of passing the back.
We have booked the room that included breakfast charges. On the day of departure i.e.  22nd July 2019, the kitchen was non-functional as lpg cylinders were exhausted. Their response was what could they do to this unforeseen occurrence!

text.text:
Terrible Experience at Hotel Rangoli – Avoid at All Costs!

I recently stayed at Hotel Rangoli, and it was by far one of the worst experiences I’ve ever had at a hotel. The staff was incredibly rude and unhelpful, showing zero professionalism or courtesy. From the moment I arrived, I regretted booking this place.

The room and toilet were filthy and clearly hadn’t been cleaned properly in ages. To make matters worse, there was no ventilation at all, making the room stuffy and uncomfortable. They even had the audacity to charge extra for using the geyser, which is something I’ve never encountered before.

Adding to the horror, street dogs were roaming around the premises freely, making it unsafe and unhygienic. There was no room cleaning or toilet cleaning facility provided during my stay, and any request to the staff was met with dismissive and rude responses.

The overall environment was chaotic, dirty, and unwelcoming. I wouldn’t recommend this hotel to anyone, not even for a night. Save yourself the trouble and book a stay somewhere else. Hotel Rangoli is a disgrace to the hospitality industry.
